      "children": [
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "data": {
            "inline": [
              {
                "type": "Words",
                "data": {
                  "value": "The line can be defined either by two points *xy1* and *xy2*, or by one point *xy1* and a *slope*."
                }
              }
            ],
            "inner": []
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "data": {
            "inline": [
              {
                "type": "Words",
                "data": {
                  "value": "This draws a straight line \"on the screen\", regardless of the x and y scales, and is thus also suitable for drawing exponential decays in semilog plots, power laws in loglog plots, etc. However, *slope* should only be used with linear scales; It has no clear meaning for all other scales, and thus the behavior is undefined. Please specify the line using the points *xy1*, *xy2* for non-linear scales."
                }
              }
            ],
            "inner": []
          }
        }
      ],
      "title": null
